social_posts.post_text:
IM. BACK. MOTHER. FRIGGERS. (That’s right, I said friggers. Come on… I’m a mom.) ⁣
⁣
It’s been eighty five months since I’ve been behind the chair and DAMN IT, LET’S DO THIS. ⁣
⁣
Whenever you’re ready to schedule an appointment to see six hundred pictures of my baby doing various works of art such as looking to the left, looking to the right, blinking, scratching her ear, and the timeless classic- spitting on herself, find your way to the link in bio and book yo shit, son. I promise to also do your hair if there’s any time left over. ⁣
⁣
#feelsgoodtobeback

Pahtnah lemme upgraaade ya 🎶 Honestly I can’t stand Beyoncé. But like… still lemme. ⁣
⁣
22” of 𝘰𝘩 𝘩𝘦𝘭𝘭𝘰 and 500 foils of 𝘢𝘸𝘸𝘸 𝘴𝘩𝘪𝘵 compliments of @bellamihairpro, @wellahairusa, oh yeah… and me. 😉 ⁣
⁣
March on over to the link in bio and book your consult. Then get a good watch because you’re gonna wanna be counting down the minutes. Heh.

Hey guys! Just wanted to share that starting today I will be implementing a $100 Black Box Fee for any clients who come in wearing the devil’s housecoat to their highlighting appointment. And I won’t lie to you, it’s going 𝘴𝘵𝘳𝘢𝘪𝘨𝘩𝘵 toward my pain and suffering. ⁣
⁣
Alright yo here comes lecture time with Jess...⁣
⁣
I’ll spare you the whole “black box color is so goddamn permanent it’s like if shoe polish were a tattoo that you would inevitably come to regret with a fiery rage” and get right down to brass tacks...⁣
⁣
The money you are saving putting this garbage on your head will be paid for in spades trying to take it out later. ⁣
⁣
𝘛𝘩𝘦 𝘮𝘰𝘯𝘦𝘺 𝘺𝘰𝘶 𝘢𝘳𝘦 𝘴𝘢𝘷𝘪𝘯𝘨 𝘱𝘶𝘵𝘵𝘪𝘯𝘨 𝘵𝘩𝘪𝘴 𝘨𝘢𝘳𝘣𝘢𝘨𝘦 𝘰𝘯 𝘺𝘰𝘶𝘳 𝘩𝘦𝘢𝘥 𝘸𝘪𝘭𝘭 𝘣𝘦 𝘱𝘢𝘪𝘥 𝘧𝘰𝘳 𝘪𝘯 𝘴𝘱𝘢𝘥𝘦𝘴 𝘵𝘳𝘺𝘪𝘯𝘨 𝘵𝘰 𝘵𝘢𝘬𝘦 𝘪𝘵 𝘰𝘶𝘵 𝘭𝘢𝘵𝘦𝘳. ⁣
⁣
Let’s try it this way. Say your teasylights normally hit ya for $300. An investment for sure. But what about when you come in with something on your hair that prevents you from getting the color you want. But you have to do it anyway, because you need that tiny bit of color change for the next few times you’ll also get a tiny bit of color change. So instead of your $300 color cost, you now spent 4 visits at $300 a pop trying to get the same result you should’ve gotten at the original $300. So you bought a $12 home color (I’m guessing, it’s been like 100 years since I box colored my hair), to avoid paying $75 for a professional color. You saved $63, you smart l’il spender! Ok now let’s take the $1200 you spent over the 4 hair appointments it took to get that box color to lift, now subtract the cost of the $75 it would’ve taken for professional hair color instead of box color, plus the $300 for the 𝘰𝘯𝘦 session it took to get your highlight goals, subtract all that from what you 𝘢𝘤𝘵𝘶𝘢𝘭𝘭𝘺 spent, and you spent $837 𝘤𝘰𝘮𝘱𝘭𝘦𝘵𝘦𝘭𝘺 𝘶𝘯𝘯𝘦𝘤𝘦𝘴𝘴𝘢𝘳𝘺 dollars. ⁣
⁣
So, just don’t do it. Just don’t.

Let ol’ Aunt Jess learn ya on some basic sales gospel (yes our job is in sales whether the word makes you cringe or not): ⁣
⁣
𝘐𝘧 𝘪𝘵’𝘴 𝘯𝘰𝘵 𝘴𝘱𝘦𝘯𝘵 𝘸𝘪𝘵𝘩 𝘺𝘰𝘶, 𝘪𝘵’𝘴 𝘴𝘱𝘦𝘯𝘵 𝘴𝘰𝘮𝘦𝘸𝘩𝘦𝘳𝘦 𝘦𝘭𝘴𝘦.⁣
⁣
One mo’ ‘gen-⁣
⁣
𝐈𝐟 𝐢𝐭’𝐬 𝐧𝐨𝐭 𝐬𝐩𝐞𝐧𝐭 𝐰𝐢𝐭𝐡 𝐲𝐨𝐮, 𝐢𝐭’𝐬 𝐬𝐩𝐞𝐧𝐭 𝐬𝐨𝐦𝐞𝐰𝐡𝐞𝐫𝐞 𝐞𝐥𝐬𝐞. ⁣
⁣
Now, regardless of whether or not this idea makes you picture yourself with a short-sleeve dress shirt with a really short necktie and a six-hair combover (I think I’m inadvertently describing Colin Farrell in Horrible Bosses), our paychecks are determined by our sales. Nothing else. Zilch. Nada. And whatever else the young people use for 𝘯𝘰𝘵 𝘢 𝘥𝘢𝘮𝘯 𝘵𝘩𝘪𝘯𝘨. ⁣
⁣
So if we decide who will and won’t buy our services before we even meet them based solely on our assumptions of their disposable money, well… what the fuck? ⁣
⁣
How many clients come to you looking like the Rose’s opulently bitchy mother from Titanic? None? How many clients come to you looking like somebody’s hungover soccer mom? 𝘗𝘳𝘰𝘣𝘣𝘣𝘣𝘢𝘣𝘭𝘺 a lot of them. ⁣
⁣
So what’s my point?⁣
⁣
If you assume someone’s long-term (shit, even 𝘴𝘩𝘰𝘳𝘵-term) spending potential in your business based on quick observations you think you valiantly gumshoed together, your ass is gonna end up broke. ⁣
⁣
And every once in awhile, you might just save someone [from their families holding a weird intervention for them]. ⁣
⁣
Everyone’s spending somewhere, don’t decide who will spend it on you.

𝐈𝐭 👏🏻 𝐅𝐞𝐞𝐥𝐬 👏🏻 𝐒𝐨 👏🏻 𝐆𝐨𝐨𝐝 👏🏻 𝐓𝐨 👏🏻 𝐁𝐞 👏🏻 𝐁𝐚𝐜𝐤 👏🏻⁣
⁣
Now… who’s ready to lie to their peers about what grows out of their head? 🙋🏻‍♀️🙋🏻‍♀️⁣

Seeing this picture is reminding me that it’s been 𝘸𝘢𝘺 too long since I’ve taught a brunette class. *sigh* Maybe it’s time to start the ol’ engine up again… 🤔🤔🤔⁣
⁣
In the meantime… this color tho, amirite? Couldn’t have had a better model to showcase this technique. All that dimension in under 15 foils. ⁣
⁣
Ya betta ax somebahdy 💁🏻‍♀️💁🏻‍♀️

Can you say 𝘣𝘢𝘣𝘦? Because I sure can! ⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
Seriously, I can… it’s one word, and I’m 37 years old.

Sometimes you’re missing fullness in your ends because you need a good cut. Sometimes, well, God just wants you to have fine ends. ⁣
⁣
Fear not! *𝘴𝘩𝘢𝘬𝘦𝘴 𝘧𝘪𝘯𝘨𝘦𝘳 𝘵𝘰𝘸𝘢𝘳𝘥 𝘵𝘩𝘦 𝘴𝘬𝘺 𝘢𝘯𝘥 𝘶𝘴𝘦𝘴 𝘸𝘩𝘢𝘵𝘦𝘷𝘦𝘳 𝘷𝘰𝘪𝘤𝘦 𝘐 𝘪𝘮𝘢𝘨𝘪𝘯𝘦 𝘉𝘦𝘯𝘫𝘢𝘮𝘪𝘯 𝘍𝘳𝘢𝘯𝘬𝘭𝘪𝘯 𝘩𝘢𝘥* There’s hope for you sticking it to your friends’ hair after all. Idk, maybe you’re petty like that. Who am I to judge. ⁣
⁣
Just two cute lil rows of @bellami volume wefts and 𝐁𝐎𝐎𝐘𝐀𝐇!… 𝘵𝘩𝘪𝘴 hot stuff. Suck it, old hair. We’re hot now. ⁣
⁣
Mosey on up to the link in bio, and book your extension consult. I’m sure there’s an ex somewhere you’d love to piss off. ⁣
⁣
Man, there’s a lot of revenge in my hair posts. I swear I’m a happy person. 😏

Let me explain why that bomb hair service is more affordable than you think.⁣
⁣
Let’s say you spend $6 on Starbucks a day (that’s right, I’m talking to you). In one month, that’s $186. But in 𝘵𝘸𝘰 months, which is the average hair appointment cycle, your Starbucks Fund is up to $372. ⁣
⁣
Sister, that’s your entire bougie hair appointment. Paid for. Deposited to the bank of Conglomerate Coffee, when it should be deposited to the bank of Holy Shit, Who Tf Is That Bitch (spoiler alert: it’s you). ⁣
⁣
Not a yuppy coffee girl? Alright, let’s sub it out. Three days a week you spend $35 on Door Dash. Twice a month you spend $80 on drinks (back in my day if you were paying for them you weren’t doing it right *𝘣𝘢 𝘥𝘶𝘮 𝘵𝘴𝘴*). Once a month you spend an average accumulation of $271 on shit you don’t need, according to Consumer Reports (I made that up but it felt right). ⁣
⁣
You want the hair. You’ve been scrolling, and Pinning, and screenshotting for months, wishing you could win the lottery without playing it (no, just me?). What you 𝘥𝘪𝘥𝘯’𝘵 realize is no, you’re not a broke bitch, Janice. You’re just out there making it rain on the wrong thing. You’re supposed to make it rain on 𝘮𝘦. ⁣
⁣
The point of this post isn’t to tell you to give up all your little joys to be able to afford a good hairstylist. It’s that you most likely 𝘤𝘢𝘯 afford it if you want to. ⁣
⁣
DoorDash: short-lived yumminess and not having to get off the couch for an extra half hour. A good hairstylist: I mean, you’ve 𝘴𝘦𝘦𝘯 Pretty Woman, for Gods sake. You can 𝘭𝘪𝘵𝘦𝘳𝘢𝘭𝘭𝘺 get a French twist and make friends with rich people. Can Starbucks make you rich friends? It cannot. ⁣
⁣
It’s your money. What ya wanna do with it? No seriously, tell me, I don’t like a cliffhanger. 😏⁣
⁣
Spend wisely, my friends.
𝐁𝐨𝐮𝐭 (𝘤𝘭𝘢𝘱) 𝐭𝐡𝐚𝐭 (𝘤𝘭𝘢𝘱) 𝐝𝐚𝐦𝐧 (𝘤𝘭𝘢𝘱) 𝐛𝐫𝐮 (𝘤𝘭𝘢𝘱) 𝐧𝐞𝐭𝐭𝐞 (𝘤𝘭𝘢𝘱) 𝐥𝐢𝐢𝐢𝐢𝐢𝐢𝐢𝐢𝐢𝐢𝐢𝐢-(𝘬𝘦𝘦𝘱 𝘩𝘰𝘭𝘥𝘪𝘯𝘨 𝘪𝘵)-𝐢𝐢𝐢𝐢𝐢𝐢𝐢𝐢𝐢𝐢𝐟𝐞. (𝘉𝘳𝘦𝘢𝘵𝘩𝘦). 😮‍💨

⁣
Once upon a time there was a girl named @mamawhomanifests (To be clear, her birth certificate does not actually read “@mamawhomanifests”. Sigh.)⁣
⁣
Anyway, @mamawhomanifests (Jamie, her name is Jamie) had like 600 businesses. Each one stemmed from her love for the one before it. She fucking crushed them all, it was the most awesome thing to watch. Even awesome-er to experience first-hand. Her passion for what she did oozed through her pores like, well, something that would ooze through a pore, but not in a gross way even though I’m drawing a blank on what could ooze through a pore that isn’t gross. ⁣
She offered her skills to any and every woman thirsty to grow in their careers and their lives. She was thriving. 𝘞𝘦 were thriving. ⁣
⁣
So, naturally, it came as no surprise when the latest venture donning Jamie’s stamp had us all instinctively flocking like the salmon of Capistrano. A deep-diving, growth-inducing style of coaching. High Vibe Money Mama. *𝘊𝘩𝘦𝘧’𝘴 𝘬𝘪𝘴𝘴*. Jamie’s program boasts an undeniable confidence in its ability to push you past your own limits and chip the corroded layers of dust and debris off of what is most certainly a Boss Bitch waiting to bitch bossily. ⁣
⁣
Can I want in on this any more than I already do? 𝘏𝘢𝘳𝘥 𝘯𝘰. So when the Growth Guru herself opened her heart and her program to one lucky scholarship recipient, girl… I’m on this shit like white on rice. ⁣
⁣
Let me tell you what this opportunity would mean to me. Jamie is a powerhouse. She emanates strength, creativity, and most importantly- 𝘵𝘩𝘦 𝘳𝘦𝘮𝘪𝘯𝘥𝘦𝘳 𝘰𝘧 𝘮𝘺 𝘰𝘸𝘯 𝘱𝘰𝘵𝘦𝘯𝘵𝘪𝘢𝘭 𝘵𝘰 𝘥𝘰 𝘵𝘩𝘦 𝘦𝘹𝘢𝘤𝘵 𝘴𝘢𝘮𝘦 𝘵𝘩𝘪𝘯𝘨. It’s crazy how we forget our own abilities. 𝘐 forget 𝘮𝘺 abilities. My massive reservoir of what could be, waiting for the reminder that it’s there. ⁣
⁣
Jamie is that reminder. ⁣
⁣
So i hopefully fling my hat into the ring for this amazing opportunity to learn from the best. To 𝘨𝘳𝘰𝘸 𝘸𝘪𝘵𝘩 the best. ⁣For me, for my sweet angel. Mama will lead the way, baby girl. 
⁣
I’m ready. ⁣
⁣.

I mean 𝐂𝐎𝐌𝐄 𝐎𝐍𝐍𝐍𝐍𝐍 😍😍😍⁣
⁣
Get your ass to the link in my bio and book your extension consult. It’s like… 𝘸𝘢𝘺𝘺𝘺𝘺 less scary than you think it is. Well I mean, I get pretty winded coming up the steps because I’m an out-of-shape 37 year-old, that’s surely a scary sight. It’ll probably be sweatier than any other professional consultation you’ve had. More labored breathing. Hell, if you ask me that’s just another selling point. Name something that could possibly make you feel 𝘭𝘦𝘴𝘴 insecure than a damp service provider with melted makeup in desperate need of albuterol. Confidence gold. ⁣
⁣
K, go book. ❤️✌🏻

Short hair? Nope, haven’t seen her. 🥸⁣
⁣
Like shaving your head when you’re a fugitive, but in reverse. ⁣
⁣
Link in bio to change your identity before they get ya. 🕵🏻‍♂️👮‍♂️⁣
⁣

It is 𝘢𝘣𝘴𝘰𝘭𝘶𝘵𝘦𝘭𝘺 𝘪𝘮𝘱𝘦𝘳𝘢𝘵𝘪𝘷𝘦 that, when you have a client who looks like a Victoria’s Secret Angel, her hair be conducive to said look. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Yeah, I think we nailed that shit.

I’ll keep this short and sweet-⁣
⁣
If you’re 𝐜𝐡𝐚𝐫𝐠𝐢𝐧𝐠 the big bucks. You better be 𝐬𝐞𝐫𝐯𝐢𝐧𝐠 the big bucks. If your client doesn’t walk out of there feeling like they just left the Four Seasons of hair appointments… ya done fucked up. ⁣
⁣
Good stylists are a dime a dozen. So ask yourself- why you? ⁣
⁣
Figure out the answer, then 𝘮𝘢𝘬𝘦 𝘪𝘵 𝘣𝘦𝘵𝘵𝘦𝘳. 💪🏻

Alright now, everybody get out a pen and paper and write this down verbatim. 𝘝𝘦𝘳𝘣𝘢𝘵𝘪𝘮, 𝘐 𝘴𝘢𝘺! ⁣
⁣
𝐑𝐞𝐜𝐤𝐥𝐞𝐬𝐬 𝐛𝐥𝐨𝐧𝐝𝐢𝐧𝐠 𝐰𝐢𝐥𝐥 𝐜𝐨𝐬𝐭 𝐲𝐨𝐮 𝐦𝐨𝐫𝐞 𝐭𝐡𝐚𝐧 𝐦𝐨𝐧𝐞𝐲. ⁣
⁣
Clients, stylists… this reminder discriminates against neither. If you’ve ever watched the quick death of enthusiasm on your stylists face at the sight of your blonde inspo pic, please scroll back up and give that visual another look. We don’t hold distain for joy and general client happiness, we simply prefer for you to keep your hair. It’s that simple. If we tell you you shouldn’t do it… don’t fucking do it. Not by that stylist, not by another stylist who may not yet have the confidence needed to tell you what you need to hear. Not by anyone. Pick a different goal, and keep your hair. ⁣
⁣
Stylists- the best way to strengthen any muscle, just like the one needed to decisively deny a service that would leave a mark on your integrity, is through repetition. Say it shakily, as long as you say it. “𝐍𝐨.” Say it like your reputation is on the line. Say it like the fate of your guests hair is on the line. It is.⁣
⁣
I’ve had clients mad at me for denying their request, and I’ve had clients mad at me for leaving their hair in shit condition. Trust me when I say one of them is far worse than the other. ⁣
⁣
In conclusion: 𝐓𝐇𝐄𝐑𝐄 𝐀𝐑𝐄 𝐎𝐓𝐇𝐄𝐑 𝐁𝐄𝐀𝐔𝐓𝐈𝐅𝐔𝐋 𝐂𝐎𝐋𝐎𝐑𝐒 𝐁𝐄𝐒𝐈𝐃𝐄𝐒 𝐅𝐔𝐂𝐊𝐈𝐍𝐆 𝐁𝐋𝐎𝐍𝐃𝐄. ⁣
⁣
Thank you for attending my Ted talk.

If you wanna win me over, come in and let me change literally everything you have on your head. ⁣
⁣
I mean sure, you’re gorgeous and all, but, like….. fun for 𝘮𝘦.

Social media is, like… 𝘣𝘦𝘺𝘰𝘯𝘥 a gift for your business. But feeling like you can’t opt out of it without your bottom line being effected is a ragingly overwhelming feeling for someone like me. ⁣
⁣
That’s all.

Let’s quit pretending it’s not about to be sexy beach hair season. You know it, I know it, your hair knows you know it.⁣.. 👀
⁣
20” of @bellamihairpro volume wefts and a lil’ wave of the color wand- bam, bitch. 𝘉𝘢𝘮, 𝘐 𝘴𝘢𝘺!

Coming back from maternity leave has been hard. The growing pains I expected versus how I actually feel, well, they rank differently.⁣
⁣
We throw the word 𝘣𝘢𝘭𝘢𝘯𝘤𝘦 around like a beach ball on Memorial Day- finding your 𝘣𝘢𝘭𝘢𝘯𝘤𝘦, work-life 𝘣𝘢𝘭𝘢𝘯𝘤𝘦, blah blah blah fucking 𝘣𝘢𝘭𝘢𝘯𝘤𝘦. But finding my footing after waking up one day as an entirely new human being, well… it’s a lot harder than I thought. Like… 𝘳𝘦𝘢𝘭𝘭𝘺 hard. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
So some days I just can’t do it. Like, any of it. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Sometimes the idea of posting on social media in order to get my career back to what it was pre-baby seems cruelly, and comically, ironic. Some days I just can’t do it. Lots of days I just can’t do it. The pressure you feel as a new mom is something the military could use to torture an enemy spy into giving up literally anything. You want my routing number? Here ya go. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Some days, many days, I just can’t do it. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
So consider this my reminder to myself, to you- whatever hat needs to get put back on the shelf, if even for just a moment- it’s okay to take a break. You fucking deserve it. ⁣⁣

Don’t get me wrong, custom extension color is literally the tits (no, 𝘭𝘪𝘵𝘦𝘳𝘢𝘭𝘭𝘺. 𝐋𝐢𝐭𝐞𝐫𝐚𝐥𝐥𝐲.) but sometimes a hot bitch comes in and just wants to match her natural, and ya know what… that’s frickin’ cool too. ⁣
⁣
Am I jealous that she doesn’t have the grays of a 75 year old that need constant covering? Maybe. But whatever, this isn’t about me despite the fact that I wholly made it about me.⁣
⁣
Recap: natural color with no need to cover grays bc she’s a rude af, soft volume, believable length. ⁣
⁣
Jess “The Trifecta” Dworniczak. Oh wait, I made it about me again. *calls therapist* ⁣

By the time your eyes sweep across these words, the time I’ve written them has long past. Because as I write this, it’s late, and I’m mid-nighttime routine of getting in bed before my husband, playing my no-brain-cells-required bubble game on one of my few lifelines to the outside world, and being lulled to sleep to the familiar soundtrack of my own thoughts of unworthiness, disappointment, and general failure.⁣
⁣
It’s been ten months since the absolute love of my life was brought into this world. Ten whole months. Surely this should have long-since subsided, right? How long can I lean on the “my hormones have just been flipped on their head” routine? At what point am I just an unhappy, selfish, inadequate mother? This must be it.⁣
⁣
Postpartum depression, anxiety, and even psychosis are not the temporary hormonal shock you may think they are. Because as biological adjustment inevitably settles, the thick, palpable reality of grief very quickly replaces it. You thought you were prepared for your own death, who you once were, but listen to me closely when I tell you you are 𝐧𝐨𝐭. A convicted criminal may survive the first week of a prison sentence with hopeful optimism of their own strength, as will you. But as time rolls on, the psychosis of your own head, the physical process of grief and acceptance will start to eat you alive. Your own brain will turn on you. You will start to believe the things it says. You are a new person, a tired, hungry, dirty, broke, lonely, emotionally bankrupt person. Your spouse will help the best they can, but you are alone. You’ve never been more alone. Alone in your grief, the loss of your own identity. You are a prisoner losing the hopeful optimism of your own strength.⁣
⁣
Please know that I don’t write this a a veiled plea for help, although help will always be an invaluable word. I write this because postpartum depression is not the endearing, short-lived life you see on tv, and the women you love are suffering in silence. ⁣It only takes one person to speak up to make a change. 
⁣
Please, mothers… it’s up to us to get this conversation started. Our lives depend on it. ⁣
⁣
This post is over now. Go send someone a text.

⁣
Think about it- let’s say you’re spending $40 a week on dumb shit. And by dumb shit, I mean something that could easily be cut out or scaled down (one less drink, one less appetizer, one less shirt at TJ Maxx). You’ve suddenly got an extra $160 a month. The average life expectancy of a balayage is 8-12 weeks, let’s split the diff at 10. Ten weeks of shaving $40 off of blind spending lands you with $400, aka a perfectly budgeted hair appointment with that stylist you’ve been wishing you could afford. ⁣
⁣
Yes, everyone’s financial situation is different. But the point of this post is to help draw your attention to how much more money you have than you think. Yeah, 𝘺𝘰𝘶. ⁣
⁣
So before you say you can’t 𝐚𝐟𝐟𝐨𝐫𝐝 something, figure out if that’s the word you wanna use. And then stop throwing your money at the wall and friggin get yourself some good hair, damn it.
